Box and Maybe <ul> <li>Generic containers for values</li> <li>Enable functional operations</li> <li>Maybe handles optional values safely</li> <li>Example:   <pre><code>// Map example
Maybe&lt;String&gt; name = Maybe.some("hello");
Maybe&lt;Integer&gt; length = name.map(s -&gt; s.length());

// FlatMap example
Maybe&lt;Maybe&lt;String&gt;&gt; nested = Maybe.some(Maybe.some("hello"));
Maybe&lt;String&gt; flattened = nested.flatMap(x -&gt; x);
</code></pre></li> </ul>

Lazy Evaluation <ul> <li>Delays computation until needed</li> <li>Avoids unnecessary calculations</li> <li>Uses memoization to cache results</li> <li>Example:   <pre><code>class Lazy&lt;T&gt; {
  private T value;
  private boolean evaluated;
  private Producer&lt;T&gt; producer;

  public T get() {
    if (!evaluated) {
      value = producer.produce();
      evaluated = true;
    }
    return value;
  }
}
</code></pre></li> </ul>
